Use the standard library
This is how to filter_by_substring of strings and substring:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that i is 0

   Do this strings' length times:
      Remember that s is item i in strings
      Remember that found is no
      Remember that j is 0

      Do this s's length times:
         When found is yes, then:
            Leave the loop
         End when

         Remember that remaining is diff of s's length and j
         When substring's length is at most remaining, then:
            Remember that matches is yes
            Remember that k is 0

            Do this substring's length times:
               When item k in s is not item k in substring, then:
                  Remember that matches is no
                  Leave the loop
               End when
               Increase k
            End do

            When matches is yes, then:
               Remember that found is yes
            End when
         End when

         Remember that s is toarray of s
         Remember that item 0 in s is item 1 in s
         Remember that s is tostring of s
         Increase j
      End do

      When found is yes, then:
         Add result to item i in strings
      End when

      Increase i
   End do

   The answer is result
Now you know

>>> filter_by_substring of [] and "a"
[]
>>> filter_by_substring of ["abc", "bacd", "cde", "array"] and "a"
["abc", "bacd", "array"]
>>> filter_by_substring of [] and "john"
[]